  "texts": [
    "In addition, the reward and utility optimality gaps depend on how well the dual function D(λ) is conditioned, as captured by L D, and on how sensitive an optimal policy is to the constraints, as reflected in λ ⋆ p and λ ⋆ ν.",
    "Similarly, we characterize the optimality gap of the policy π ⋆ p (λ ⋆) regarding the reward and utility functions in Theorem 4; see Appendix B.9 for proof.",
    "Theorem 4 (Reward and utility optimality: one-shot scheme).",
    "Let Assumptions 3, 4, 5, and 6 hold.",
    "Then, the reward and utility optimality gaps of the policyπ ⋆ p (λ ⋆) satisfy R-OPT(π ⋆ p (λ ⋆)) ≤ 2L D (M + β + M ∥λ ⋆ ∥ 1) ν + (M + β + M ∥λ ⋆ ∥ 1) ν U-OPT(π ⋆ p (λ ⋆)) ≤ 2L D (M + β + M ∥λ ⋆ ∥ 1) ν.Theorem 4 characterizes the optimality gap of the policy π ⋆ p (λ ⋆) regarding the reward and utility functions."
